As we know, the origin of the evolved H2 is somewhat unclear until now when alcohols are used as hole scavengers. Researchers wonder whether the H2 evolution is a water splitting reaction or a photocatalytic reforming process (Supplementary Note 5)45. In this work, no H2 was released when conducting the experiments in pure methanol, suggesting the above photocatalytic process is not a methanol decomposition reaction46,47. It is reported that H2 can also be produced through the methanol reforming reaction4CH3OH+H2O→hυ,catalystCO2+3H2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
